{
  "texts": [
    "More recently, the field has seen a significant transition from such engineered features to features learned in an end-to-end fashion by models that operate on rawlevel input or tokens (Collobert et al., 2011).",
    "However, such end-to-end models necessitate large annotated training sets, available for English but scarce for low-resource languages.",
    "This problem can be mitigated by pretraining on unannotated data.",
    "Indeed, the emergence of pretrained large language models (LLMs) inspired by the transformer architecture (Vaswani et al., 2017) led to new state-of-the-art results across various NLP tasks.",
    "Among these, encoder-only models like BERT were demonstrated to improve existing SRL benchmarks (Shi & Lin, 2019)."
  ]
}